{"type":"message","id":"6e76f2f0","parentId":"5ecbfa7a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:57:46.825Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the logs, I can see `agent-orchestrator` is running and active. The binding for agent-orchestrator IS present in the config (I can see the session `agent:agent-orchestrator:feishu:agent-orchestrator:direct:ou_d738ff68ba381582a3051f11b976c854`). So the feishu account binding IS working.\n\nThe user says the Agent编排工程师 doesn't have permission to feishu docs and bitable. This is a feishu app permission issue - the `cli_a9558a1795799bb5` app needs to be published with the right permissions. \n\nEven though the user says the permissions are configured in the Feishu console, the bot still can't access the documents - this is likely because the new app version hasn't been published yet. The `agent-orchestrator` session exists, so the binding is working, but the permissions problem persists. the specific document/bitable itself, you need to share the document with the bot directly - you can't just rely on API permissions alone. The bot needs to be added as a collaborator to that particular document in Feishu. I see the feishu doc and bitable skills are referenced in the workspace, so I should check if they're properly installed and configured for the agent-orchestrator agent to use them properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"14ace7890aede8c6f45f9aeeaa2a57cce5e925efe09007aa574264d09b9a0e88"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bupebo8jv270_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/workspace-agent-orchestrator/skills/ 2>/dev/null && ls ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6683,"output":335,"cacheRead":71680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78698,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778410653309,"responseId":"064f979d63197d17eadad1c1e2d53489"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e1121f3","parentId":"6e76f2f0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:57:46.905Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bupebo8jv270_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"claw-swarm\nopenclaw-multi-agent-hq-builder\norchestrator-v4\nswarm-control-feishu\nskills"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":38,"aggregated":"claw-swarm\nopenclaw-multi-agent-hq-builder\norchestrator-v4\nswarm-control-feishu\nskills","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778410666904}}
{"type":"message","id":"9aea9378","parentId":"2e1121f3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:58:11.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that `agent-orchestrator` has skills in its workspace: `claw-swarm`, `openclaw-multi-agent-hq-builder`, `orchestrator-v4`, `swarm-control-feishu`. These look like skills for multi-agent orchestration.\n\nThe feishu-docs permission issue - the user says they've configured the permissions in feishu dev console, but the bot still doesn't have permission. The logs confirm agent-orchestrator is running and active.\n\nThe problem might be that the `agent-orchestrator` workspace has `feishu-doc` skill but it might not be properly configured, OR the feishu app permissions haven't been published/released.\n\n\nI notice the workspace also contains skills that reference `openclaw-lark`, but that extension symlink points to an empty directory - so it seems like the lark extension was installed but removed, and now the skills there can't find what they need.\n\nThis could be causing the permissions failures, though the agent itself is still active. I should ask whether the user actually published the app in the Feishu console after updating permissions, since that's a common step people miss - you need to publish before the changes take effect.\n\nBut looking at the diagnostic logs more carefully, I'm seeing something odd - `agent-orchestrator` is showing up as `agent:agent-orchestrator:main`, which suggests it's running as the main agent rather than its own separate process. And I don't see `feishu[agent-orchestrator]` in the startup logs at all, which means the agent-orchestrator WebSocket connection for that account never actually started up. The account is configured but not connected.\n\nSo there are two separate problems here - the feishu app itself may not have been published with the right permissions, and the agent-orchestrator account's WebSocket connection isn't even established. The user might be confused about which issue they're facing, since the bot appears online but the feishu API calls would fail due to missing permissions if the app wasn't properly published.\n\nI should clarify with the user - is the agent-orchestrator bot responding in chat, and when it tries to access documents, what error message specifically comes back? That would help narrow down whether the problem is the unpublished app or the bot's WebSocket connection.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the issue might be that the feishu app itself doesn't have the right permissions published - the agent-orchestrator account is configured correctly, but the feishu app's permission expansion probably wasn't approved and published yet.\n","thinkingSignature":"1ebcecd35bd10768e11b5d46f55d3fb3a62f9640c01357f52edd17d3b26e0409"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n配置层面没问题，agent-orchestrator 在运行中。\n\n**但我发现一个问题：**\n\n日志里没有看到 `feishu[agent-orchestrator]` WebSocket 启动的记录，说明这个账号的飞书 WebSocket 连接可能没有建立。\n\n**两层检查：**\n\n1. **飞书开放平台 → 版本发布**：`cli_a9558a1795799bb5` 必须在「版本管理与发布」里创建并发布版本，否则应用权限不生效。\n\n2. **具体某个文档/多维表格的分享权限**：即使 API 权限开通了，机器人要读写具体文档，还需要在文档的「分享→添加成员→机器人账号」里把它加进去。\n\n你现在是在哪个文档/多维表格上测试的？是它直接报错 `permission denied`，还是什么情况？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":186,"output":679,"cacheRead":78272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79137,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778410666908,"responseId":"064f97ab36bdff246a14cc23c468f4ea"}}
