{"type":"message","id":"d7b96ca2","parentId":"ceb7159c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T11:08:32.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying that they installed the official Feishu CLI via npm (`@larksuiteo/fessel` or similar official Feishu CLI tool), not the openclaw-lark community plugin. \n\nThe official Feishu CLI is `@larksuiteo/fessel` or `@feishu/cli` - it's a separate npm package that lets you call Feishu APIs directly from command line.\n\nSo the question is: why doesn't OpenClaw's Agent have access to these Feishu API capabilities that the official CLI has?\n\nThe answer is: OpenClaw agents use Skills to access Feishu APIs. \n\nThe official Feishu CLI is a separate tool on the system that the user personally installed and can use directly, but the AI agent running within OpenClaw doesn't automatically gain access to it just because it's installed on the same machine. The AI agent would need to either call it through exec commands or have a dedicated Feishu API skill configured. It sounds like the user previously had an integration that made these Feishu API capabilities accessible to their agent, and they're asking why that connection is no longer working.\n","thinkingSignature":"61287976a4612dcdad71bc7304b5f91dba6ee9885168dcc0babea9124fd32d7e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了。你装的是飞书官方 CLI 工具（`@larksuiteo/fessel` 或类似），可以直接调飞书 API。\n\n但 **OpenClaw Agent 是独立的 AI 进程**，它能调什么工具取决于：\n1. 系统层有没有对应的 Skill 文件\n2. Agent 的 workspace 里有没有那个工具\n3. 有没有配置好凭据\n\n你之前能让 AI 创建飞书文档，是因为某个 Agent 的 workspace 里配了飞书 CLI 的调用方式。\n\n**现在的问题变成了：**\n`agent-orchestrator` 的 workspace 里装的 Skill 是 `create-feishu-doc`（clawhub 版本），但它底层也是调飞书 API，需要飞书应用有权限。\n\n你说的那个飞书 CLI 在哪个路径？我来帮你看它是怎么配置的，然后在 agent-orchestrator 的 workspace 里把它用起来。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4565,"output":406,"cacheRead":74240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79211,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite"